cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

This paper is about creating a corpus for sentiment analysis in Norwegian language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also mentions pre-processing the corpus using UDPipe, which is a tool for tokenization, tagging, and parsing, indicating that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the SANT initiative, which seeks to provide resources and tools for sentiment analysis and opinion mining, indicating that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
